description: There are three things you'll learn being a Time Lord: One, pizza is never delivered fast enough. Second, being old isn't so bad. Third... no matter how much you like the 20th and 21st centuries, there is something STYLISH and just plain AWESOME about earlier times! Click here for Unisex Shirts!

name: Tech Support (Ladies Cut)
description: I’m not here to listen to you whine. I’m not here to argue with you. I’m not here to take blame for your stupidity. I’m here to fix your computer. I don’t care how it got broken, or why you want it fixed, or even what you think the problem is. Because if you knew what the problem was, and how to fix it, you wouldn’t have called me. So stop fighting me, stop acting like you can operate anything more complicated than a Sit-n-Spin, and just listen. Do that, and we’ll both get out of this alive.

name: Never Forget - Ladies Cut
description: This shirt is a masterpiece, capturing the dedication of Imperial Stormtroopers as they restore order to our chaotic galaxy. It's perfectly normal to gaze at this shirt and feel a measure of pride (or disgust, if you're a rebel) but be warned: despite its patriotic appeal, the "Never Forget" shirt is NOT a valid visual aid for any history term paper. Granted, we know you think the capture of Kashyyyk was a pivotal moment in time, but your teacher is probably going to expect you to mention something about Gettysburg instead. Likewise, you won't earn any points discussing the merits of clone troopers vs. battle droids. I'm sorry, man... but school is war, and war is hell.

name: Sector 2814 - Ladies Tank Top
description:
Yes, the badge on this shirt will display your duty to protect Earth and its surrounding area from intergalactic enemies. Yes, the shimmering green hue and glow-in-the-dark design will command respect from all those around you… or at least the two people out of every crowd who will get the reference. Yes, it’s even something that might keep you warm on a long flight to another galaxy (provided it’s not too windy in the vacuum of space). However, we regret to inform you that this shirt will not suddenly materialize around your torso when you hold up your ring and recite the oath. You will need to physically open your dresser drawer and pull its cotton-blend frame around your body manually. Cosmic City greatly regrets any inconvenience this may cause you, our valued customer.
 
GLOWS IN THE DARK!!!

name: Professor Parking - Ladies Cut
description: So you can turn playing cards into explosive projectiles?  Heal a wound seconds after it's been opened?  Control the weather with a single thought?  Oh sure, that's pretty cool.  Remember, however, you're still the students.  Only the teacher has the power to create a parking space right at the front of any lot!

description: What is "The Power of DeLancie"?  Is it found in a noncorporeal being that torments starships?  Is it a curse that destroys stages at science fiction conventions? Whatever it is, The Power of DeLancie is able to make this shirt glow in the dark-- and that's just a sample of its might!

description:
If there's something amiss
nearby to your hamlet
Whom will you telegraph?
Spectral Smashers!

If there's some odd matter
and you surely can't stand it
Whom will you telegraph?
Spectral Smashers!

We aren't bothered by mere apparitions!

name: Sci Fi Element
description:
Scandium is a remarkable element, an alloy of which is often used in the construction of aircraft components.  More fundamental than that, it can form “Sci-Fi”, which is the basis of life as we know it.  Because frankly, life just isn’t the same if you don’t factor in the lightsabers, time portals, and the occasional android.  Put the “Science” back in science fiction!

Cosmic City is not responsible for any poor Chemistry grades resulting from an improper use of this shirt.

name: Steam Beetle
description: If you’re the type who thinks that anything can be SteamPunk-ified by wrapping it in leather and adding rivets, hold on to your flight cap!  This might appear to be just a schematic for a robot beetle, but adjust your googles a bit and look closer.  The images is derived from a design that, were it actually built, would actually be a working machine.  Yes, that’s right, we’re actually sending you the plans to build your own steampunk robot insects.  And you thought Santa was cool?  We’re like Santa Claus, if he was holding a keg and drove a time machine.

name: I'm Tech Support, Shut Up and Do What I Say
description: I’m not here to listen to you whine.  I’m not here to argue with you.  I’m not here to take blame for your stupidity.  I’m here to fix your computer.  I don’t care how it got broken, or why you want it fixed, or even what you think the problem is.  Because if you knew what the problem was, and how to fix it, you wouldn’t have called me.  So stop fighting me, stop acting like you can operate anything more complicated than a Sit-n-Spin, and just listen.  Do that, and we’ll both get out of this alive.

name: Midnight Moon
description: It was a crisp November night.  Sounds traveled far in the still air, yet I never heard it approach.  Suddenly, I was face to face with the beast.  It stared into my very soul, then raised its muzzle to the heavens and called to the moon.  The sound ripped through my body, turning my nerves into jelly.  It was the most beautiful thing I’d ever seen.  Especially because the next thing I saw was him tearing into my entrails like they were a Big Mac, because that wasn’t beautiful at all.

name: Star Trek Galileo Mighty Wallet
description: It comfortably seats seven on medium-length voyages through space, the Shuttlecraft Galileo is the minivan of the 23rd century.  Sadly, Spock is just as likely as your mom to tell you to behave or he'll turn this thing around and head back to the ship.  He also controls the stereo too, so I sure hope you like Mozart.  Wallet is made of tyvek, to make it water-resistant and extra durable-- even against attack by giant Taureans.

name: Star Trek Enterprise Mighty Wallet
description: It's happened again.  Your eye is twitching, that vein on your forehead is throbbing, and somehow you just can't see straight.  Once again, you're dealt the pain of having some halfwit try to tell you the joke about how there's no bathroom on the Enterprise.  It wasn't funny the first time you heard it, and it's still not funny... but at least this time you can whip out your trusty Enterprise wallet and show your friend that not only does your favorite starship have a bathroom, but given the chance, they'd be the ones assigned to clean it.  Wallet is made of tyvek, to make it extra durable and water resistant.

name: Wonder Woman Mighty Wallet
description: Okay, so you can deflect bullets and arrows with your gauntlets.  And your magic lasso will force anyone to tell the truth, sure.  You can fly in your invisible plane, no problem.  I have no problem believing any of that.  Please tell me, though, WHERE on that costume is there any space to hold a wallet?  Even if the wallet were made from Tyvek, to make it durable, light, and water-resistant...

name: Superman Mighty Wallet
description: It's called a "wallet" and you use it to carry money.  This is a good idea, because even though taking a lump of coal and compressing it into a diamond is a great party trick, it's just not practical when you feel like stopping for a slushie.  Not only that, but making change is a pain and hey, someone might actually want to use that coal.  Wallet is made from Tyvek, to make it durable, light, and water-resistant... because not all of us are invulnerabe.
